==German==

===Etymology===
From the Middle High German ''Wodan'', from Old High German ''Wotan'', from Proto-Germanic ''wōdono'' (raging, inspired), from reconstructed Proto-Indo-European ''wet-'', ''to inspire''.

===Proper noun===
'''Wotan'''

# A deity of the old Germanic religion, and of modern German reconstructions of this religion.  See [[Odin]].